sentences: Kareem "Biggs" Burke (born January 19, 1974) is an American entrepreneur, record executive, and film producer.
Kareem Burke was born in Harlem, New York on January 19, 1974.
In 2003, his brother Robert E. Burke III was murdered in the Bronx.
In 1995, Burke co-founded the record label Roc-A-Fella Records with Shawn "Jay-Z" Carter and Damon "Dame" Dash.
Burke also co-founded Rocawear in 1999, with Carter and Dash.
In 2004, Roc-A-Fella Records was purchased by Def Jam Recordings (which had previously only owned half of the company).
And in late 2005, Carter bought Dash and Burke out of their stake in Rocawear.
In 2018, Burke executive produced the film, O.G. which premiered on HBO on February 23, 2019.

In February 2019, it was announced that Burke had signed Saint Jhn to his management company, Circle of Success.
In August 2020, Biggs took to social media to announce an Emmy nomination for “It's a Hard Truth, Ain't It”.

sentences: On June 4, 2012, Burke was sentenced to five years in prison after pleading guilty to conspiring to distribute more than 100 kilos of marijuana.
In November 2015, Burke was released from prison after serving four years of his sentence.
